Actress Nkechi Blessing Sunday has said selling her Range Rover to complete her house was the best decision she made in 2021. The movie star made this known in a bid to advise her fans and followers on setting aright their priorities in the New Year. The thespian, who had shared the news of her house alongside its photos in December 2021, argued a car isn’t an achievement but merely a necessity. She however said people should do whatever works for them as she was barely unearthing her opinion which she noted wasn’t up for a debate.   Why I took five years to release sophomore album, by Seyi…     ‘How to use your ‘Bakassi’ to lure Yoruba men at parties’     My driver missing with car – Biodun Okeowo   - Advertisement - Nkechi wrote: “The best decision I made in 2021 was selling my Range Rover to complete this beauty behind me. “Thank God for the space bus I bought for my mum. Shey landlady for Dey trek by now. “It’s 2022, try set your priorities right. A car is never an achievement but a necessity, a means of transporting you from one place to another. “This is my own opinion and I did not call for a debate. Choose whatever works for you pls..Just saying respectfully #unstoppable #ogoagbaye.”